      <div class="section">
        <h2>How to Use This Worksheet</h2>
        <p>Pick any element from the periodic table below. Copy one of these prompts, paste it into an AI chatbot, and replace <em>[element symbol]</em> with your chosen element symbol like H, Fe, or Au. After learning, mark the element as studied by clicking it. When printing, the boxes below the prompts will be blank for you to fill in your own notes.</p>

        <div class="prompt-container">
          <div class="prompt-box">
            <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyPrompt(1,this)">Copy</button>
            <h4>🔬 Meet the Element</h4>
            <div class="prompt-text" id="prompt1">
I'm a 7th grade student learning about elements. Please explain [element symbol] using simple words (6th-7th grade level). First, give me a quick 1-sentence answer about what this element is. Then explain the most important thing I should know about it. Next, compare it to something I see every day to help me understand. After that, suggest one simple way I could learn more about it. Finally, ask me a question to check if I understood.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="prompt-box">
            <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyPrompt(2,this)">Copy</button>
            <h4>📜 Discovery Detective</h4>
            <div class="prompt-text" id="prompt2">
I'm a 7th grader studying element discoveries. Tell me about [element symbol] using simple language (6th-7th grade reading level). Start with a quick sentence about who found it and when. Then share the most interesting fact about how it was discovered. Compare the discovery to finding something surprising (like an analogy). Give me one way I could research more about this discovery. End by asking me a question to see if I learned something new.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="prompt-box">
            <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyPrompt(3,this)">Copy</button>
            <h4>🏠 Real Life Hunter</h4>
            <div class="prompt-text" id="prompt3">
I'm in 7th grade and want to find [element symbol] in my daily life. Use simple words (6th-7th grade level). Start by quickly naming one common place I'd find this element. Then explain why it's useful in that item. Compare how this element works to something I already understand. Suggest one thing I could look for at home or school that contains this element. Finish with a question to test if I can spot this element around me.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="prompt-box">
            <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyPrompt(4,this)">Copy</button>
            <h4>🎭 Element Superhero</h4>
            <div class="prompt-text" id="prompt4">
I'm a 7th grade student creating element superheroes. Help me understand [element symbol] using simple words (6th-7th grade reading level). Start with one sentence about what superpower this element would have based on its real properties. Then explain the most important real ability that gives it this power. Compare this element's "personality" to a character I might know. Give me one creative way to remember this element's special ability. End with a question to see if I can explain why this element would be a good superhero.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

